# TypeScript & code quality

## Language standards

- TypeScript **strict** everywhere
- Imports at top of file — no inline imports unless documented circular-dep exception
- Exhaustive switches: `never` in default case for union/enum switches
- Prefer existing abstractions; match surrounding naming and file structure

## Contracts (`packages/contracts`)

- Every cross-boundary artifact has a **Zod schema** + exported TS type
- LLM calls: strict JSON schemas; **re-validate server-side** after every provider response
- LLM outputs: choice-generation over freeform — lever IDs, enum choices, ValueRef handles

## Package purity

- `packages/engine`: zero Next.js/React imports — must run in worker/CLI/test without web app
- `packages/adapters`: broker polymorphism via adapter policy, not engine forks
- `apps/web`: thin orchestration — business logic in packages

## Error handling

- Fail-closed on schema violations, scope violations, and live-gate failures
- No silent catch-and-ignore on trading or verification paths
- Structured failure codes matching v1 verification shape where applicable

## File size

- Decompose files approaching ~300+ lines when adding features
- One clear responsibility per module/file
